{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1400,"text":"Hello."},{"time":2640,"text":"My name is Matthew Williams,"},{"time":4600,"text":"and I am a champion."},{"time":7520,"text":"I have won medals\nin three different sports"},{"time":10400,"text":"and national games in Canada,"},{"time":13160,"text":"competed at the international\nlevel in basketball"},{"time":16680,"text":"and was proud to represent Canada"},{"time":19760,"text":"on the world stage."}]},{"cues":[{"time":21400,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":27040,"text":"I train five days a week\nfor basketball and speed skating,"},{"time":31280,"text":"work with top quality coaches"},{"time":33680,"text":"and mental performance consultants"},{"time":36200,"text":"to be at my best in my sport."},{"time":40640,"text":"By the way, all that\nis through Special Olympics."},{"time":44600,"text":"Does that change the way you think of me"},{"time":46920,"text":"and my accomplishments?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":51240,"text":"The world does not see\nall people like me as champions."},{"time":55720,"text":"Not long ago, people like me\nwere shunned and hidden away."},{"time":62240,"text":"There has been lots of change\nsince Special Olympics began in 1968,"},{"time":67400,"text":"but in too many cases,"},{"time":69560,"text":"people with intellectual disabilities"},{"time":72400,"text":"are invisible to the wider population."},{"time":77880,"text":"People use the r-word in front of me,\nand they think it doesn't matter."},{"time":83120,"text":"That's the word \"retard\" or \"retarded\""},{"time":86200,"text":"used in a derogatory manner."},{"time":89400,"text":"They're not thinking about how much\nit hurts me and my friends."}]},{"cues":[{"time":96000,"text":"I don't want you to think\nI'm here because I'm a charity case."},{"time":99880,"text":"I am here because there is still\na big problem with the way"},{"time":103920,"text":"many people see individuals\nwith intellectual disabilities,"},{"time":109680,"text":"or, too often,"},{"time":111280,"text":"how they don't see them at all."}]},{"cues":[{"time":114480,"text":"Did you know the World Games\nhappened this year?"},{"time":118200,"text":"I was one of over 6,500 athletes\nwith intellectual disabilities"},{"time":124120,"text":"from 165 countries who competed in LA."},{"time":128960,"text":"There was over 62,000 spectators\nwatching opening ceremonies,"},{"time":134280,"text":"and there was live coverage\non TSN and ESPN."},{"time":139200,"text":"Did you even know that happened?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":143600,"text":"What do you think of\nwhen you see someone like me?"},{"time":147760,"text":"I am here today to challenge you"},{"time":150560,"text":"to look at us as equals."}]},{"cues":[{"time":155160,"text":"Special Olympics transforms\nthe self-identity of athletes"},{"time":159360,"text":"with intellectual disabilities"},{"time":161760,"text":"and the perceptions of everyone watching."},{"time":166200,"text":"For those of you who aren't familiar,"},{"time":168320,"text":"Special Olympics is for athletes\nwith intellectual disabilities."},{"time":174800,"text":"Special Olympics is separate\nfrom the Paralympics and Olympics."},{"time":180320,"text":"We offer high-quality,\nyear round sports programs"},{"time":184080,"text":"for people with intellectual disabilities"},{"time":187280,"text":"that changes lives and perceptions."},{"time":192440,"text":"This movement has changed my life"},{"time":195080,"text":"and those of so many others."},{"time":197800,"text":"And it has changed the way"},{"time":199720,"text":"the world sees people\nwith intellectual disabilities."}]},{"cues":[{"time":205480,"text":"I was born with epilepsy\nand an intellectual disability."},{"time":211280,"text":"Growing up, I played hockey\nuntil I was 12 years old."},{"time":216880,"text":"The older I got, the more I felt"},{"time":219600,"text":"it was harder to keep up\nwith everyone else,"},{"time":223000,"text":"and I was angry and frustrated."},{"time":227800,"text":"For a while, I did not play any sports,"},{"time":231320,"text":"didn't have many friends"},{"time":233240,"text":"and felt left out and sad."}]},{"cues":[{"time":238080,"text":"There was a time when people\nwith intellectual disabilities"},{"time":242520,"text":"were hidden away from society."},{"time":246880,"text":"No one thought they could\nparticipate in sports,"},{"time":250080,"text":"let alone be a valued member of society."},{"time":254880,"text":"In the 1960s, Dr. Frank Hayden,"},{"time":258640,"text":"a scientist at the University of Toronto,"},{"time":261959,"text":"was studying the effects\nof regular exercise"},{"time":265640,"text":"on the fitness levels of children\nwith intellectual disabilities."},{"time":271840,"text":"Using rigorous scientific research,"},{"time":275120,"text":"Dr. Hayden and other researchers"},{"time":277880,"text":"came to the conclusion"},{"time":279800,"text":"that it was simply the lack\nof opportunity to participate"},{"time":283840,"text":"that caused their fitness\nlevels to suffer."}]},{"cues":[{"time":288400,"text":"Lots of people doubted\nthat people with intellectual disabilities"},{"time":292800,"text":"could benefit from fitness programs"},{"time":295760,"text":"and sports competition opportunities."},{"time":299880,"text":"But pioneers like Dr. Hayden\nand Eunice Kennedy Shriver,"},{"time":304880,"text":"the founder of Special Olympics,"},{"time":307200,"text":"persevered,"},{"time":308680,"text":"and Special Olympics athletes\nhave proved them right"},{"time":312120,"text":"four and a half million times over."}]},{"cues":[{"time":315680,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":321360,"text":"Before I joined Special Olympics,"},{"time":323600,"text":"I was nervous"},{"time":325120,"text":"because I was young, shy, not confident"},{"time":329360,"text":"and didn't have many friends."},{"time":332600,"text":"When I got there, though,\neveryone was very encouraging,"},{"time":336320,"text":"supportive, and let me be myself"},{"time":339640,"text":"without being judged."},{"time":342880,"text":"Now, I am a basketball player\nand speed skater"},{"time":347120,"text":"who has competed\nat provincial, national games,"},{"time":350960,"text":"and this year made it all the way\nto the World Summer Games in LA,"},{"time":355680,"text":"where I was part of the first ever\nCanadian basketball team"},{"time":359520,"text":"to compete at World Games."}]},{"cues":[{"time":361960,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":369760,"text":"I am one of more than four and a half\nmillion athletes around the globe,"},{"time":374200,"text":"and I've heard so many similar stories."},{"time":377840,"text":"Being Special Olympics athletes"},{"time":380120,"text":"restores our pride and dignity."}]},{"cues":[{"time":385000,"text":"Special Olympics also addresses\ncritical health needs."},{"time":390400,"text":"Studies have shown that, on average,"},{"time":393440,"text":"men with intellectual disabilities"},{"time":396120,"text":"die 13 years younger than men without,"},{"time":399640,"text":"and women with intellectual disabilities"},{"time":402600,"text":"die 20 years younger than women without."},{"time":406960,"text":"Special Olympics keeps us healthy"},{"time":409440,"text":"by getting us active"},{"time":411240,"text":"and participating in sport."},{"time":413920,"text":"Also, our coaches teach us\nabout nutrition and health."},{"time":420840,"text":"Special Olympics also provides\nfree health screening"},{"time":424360,"text":"for athletes who have difficulty\ncommunicating with their doctor"},{"time":428880,"text":"or accessing health care."}]},{"cues":[{"time":433480,"text":"At the 2015 World Summer Games,"},{"time":436240,"text":"my Team Canada teammates and I\nplayed the Nigerian basketball team."},{"time":442000,"text":"The day before our game,"},{"time":443840,"text":"the Nigerian basketball team went to\nthe World Games Healthy Athlete screening,"},{"time":449520,"text":"where seven of 10 members"},{"time":451880,"text":"were given hearing aids for free"},{"time":454400,"text":"and got to hear clearly\nfor the first time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":458400,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":467160,"text":"The change in them was amazing."},{"time":470040,"text":"They were more excited,\nhappy and confident,"},{"time":474240,"text":"because their coach could\nvocally communicate with them."},{"time":477640,"text":"And they were emotional"},{"time":479440,"text":"because they could hear\nthe sounds of the basketball,"},{"time":482320,"text":"the sounds of the whistle"},{"time":484320,"text":"and the cheering fans in the stands --"},{"time":487120,"text":"sounds that we take for granted."},{"time":491640,"text":"Special Olympics is transforming more\nthan just the athlete in their sport."},{"time":496960,"text":"Special Olympics is transforming\ntheir lives off the field."},{"time":502680,"text":"This year, research findings showed"},{"time":505640,"text":"that nearly half of the adults in the US"},{"time":508600,"text":"don't know a single person\nwith an intellectual disability,"},{"time":513520,"text":"and the 44 percent of Americans"},{"time":516080,"text":"who don't have personal contact\nwith intellectual disabilities"},{"time":520520,"text":"are significantly\nless accepting and positive."}]},{"cues":[{"time":526040,"text":"Then there's the r-word,"},{"time":528200,"text":"proving that people\nwith intellectual disabilities"},{"time":531480,"text":"are still invisible"},{"time":533320,"text":"to far too many people."},{"time":537000,"text":"People use it as a casual\nterm or an insult."},{"time":540560,"text":"It was tweeted more than\nnine million times last year,"},{"time":544280,"text":"and it is deeply hurtful"},{"time":546320,"text":"to me and my four and a half million\nfellow athletes around the planet."},{"time":552640,"text":"People don't think it's insulting,"},{"time":555000,"text":"but it is."},{"time":557680,"text":"As my fellow athlete and global messenger\nJohn Franklin Stephens wrote"},{"time":563080,"text":"in an open letter to a political pundit"},{"time":566520,"text":"who used the r-word as an insult,"},{"time":570080,"text":"\"Come join us someday at Special Olympics."},{"time":573120,"text":"See if you walk away\nwith your heart unchanged.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":578160,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":587720,"text":"This year, at the 2015 World Summer Games,"},{"time":591960,"text":"people lined up for hours"},{"time":593920,"text":"to get into the final night\nof powerlifting competition."},{"time":597960,"text":"So it was standing room only\nwhen my teammate Jackie Barrett,"},{"time":602360,"text":"the Newfoundland Moose,"},{"time":604160,"text":"deadlifted 655 pounds"},{"time":607680,"text":"and lifted 611 pounds in the squat --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":611960,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":619280,"text":"setting huge new records\nfor Special Olympics."},{"time":624120,"text":"Jackie is a record holder\namong all powerlifters in Newfoundland --"},{"time":628920,"text":"not just Special Olympics,\nall powerlifters."},{"time":633920,"text":"Jackie was a huge star in LA,"},{"time":636760,"text":"and ESPN live-tweeted\nhis record-breaking lifts"},{"time":641360,"text":"and were wowed by his performance."}]},{"cues":[{"time":645480,"text":"Fifty years ago, few imagined\nindividuals with intellectual disabilities"},{"time":651320,"text":"could do anything like that."},{"time":654880,"text":"This year, 60,000 spectators filled\nthe famous LA Memorial Coliseum"},{"time":662000,"text":"to watch the opening\nceremonies of World Games"},{"time":665680,"text":"and cheer athletes from 165 countries"},{"time":669480,"text":"around the world."},{"time":671840,"text":"Far from being hidden away,"},{"time":674080,"text":"we were cheered and celebrated."},{"time":679000,"text":"Special Olympics teaches athletes"},{"time":681760,"text":"to be confident and proud of themselves."},{"time":685760,"text":"Special Olympics teaches the world"},{"time":688200,"text":"that people with intellectual disabilities"},{"time":691040,"text":"deserve respect and inclusion."}]},{"cues":[{"time":694360,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":702520,"text":"Now, I have dreams\nand achievements in my sport,"},{"time":706920,"text":"great coaches,"},{"time":708560,"text":"respect and dignity,"},{"time":711000,"text":"better health,"},{"time":712240,"text":"and I am pursuing a career\nas a personal trainer."}]},{"cues":[{"time":716200,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":723320,"text":"I am no longer hidden, bullied"},{"time":726320,"text":"and I am here doing a TED Talk."}]},{"cues":[{"time":729040,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":764240,"text":"The world is a different place\nbecause of Special Olympics,"},{"time":769600,"text":"but there is still farther to go."},{"time":772320,"text":"So the next time you see someone\nwith an intellectual disability,"},{"time":776440,"text":"I hope you will see their ability."},{"time":779480,"text":"The next time someone uses\nthe r-word near you,"},{"time":782640,"text":"I hope you will tell them\nhow much it hurts."},{"time":786000,"text":"I hope you will think about getting\ninvolved with Special Olympics."}]},{"cues":[{"time":791600,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":795240,"text":"I would like to leave you\nwith one final thought."},{"time":799320,"text":"Nelson Mandela said,"},{"time":801000,"text":"\"Sports has the power\nto change the world.\""},{"time":805040,"text":"Special Olympics is changing the world"},{"time":807920,"text":"by transforming\nfour and a half million athletes"},{"time":811520,"text":"and giving us a place to be confident,"},{"time":814320,"text":"meet friends,"},{"time":815920,"text":"not be judged"},{"time":817600,"text":"and get to feel like and be champions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":821400,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":822800,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}